sCodetector","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L852-L852"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasCodetector.mk\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">HasCodetector</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hasCodetector</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.IsCodetector\">IsCodetector</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasCodetector\">HasCodetector</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasCodetector.mk","kind":"ctor","line":851,"name":"CategoryTheory.HasCodetector.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L851-L851"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasCodetector\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">HasCodetector</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a category `C` and an object `G : C`, `G` is a codetector of `C` if\nthe functor `C(-, G)` reflects isomorphisms.\n\nWhile `IsCodetector G : Prop` is the proposition that `G` is a codetector of `C`,\nan `HasCodetector C : Prop` is the proposition that such a codetector exists.\nNote that `HasCodetector C` is a proposition. It does not designate a favored codetector\nand merely asserts the existence of one.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasCodetector","kind":"class","line":842,"name":"CategoryTheory.HasCodetector","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L842-L852"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasDetector.hasDetector\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">HasDetector</span>.<span class=\"name\">hasDetector</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span clas