/span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hasDetector</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.IsDetector\">IsDetector</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasDetector\">HasDetector</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasDetector.mk","kind":"ctor","line":839,"name":"CategoryTheory.HasDetector.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L839-L839"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.HasDetector\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">HasDetector</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a category `C` and an object `G : C`, `G` is a detector of `C` if\nthe functor `C(G, -)` reflects isomorphisms.\n\nWhile `IsDetector G : Prop` is the proposition that `G` is a detector of `C`,\nan `HasDetector C : Prop` is the proposition that 