ib/CategoryTheory/Equivalence.html#CategoryTheory.Equivalence\">≌</a> <span class=\"fn\">D</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/ObjectProperty/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.strictMap\">strictMap</a></span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Equivalence.html#CategoryTheory.Equivalence.functor\">functor</a></span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsSeparating\">IsSeparating</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsSeparating.of_equivalence","kind":"theorem","line":109,"name":"CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsSeparating.of_equivalence","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L109-L115"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsCodetecting\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">ObjectProperty</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsCodetecting</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/ObjectProperty/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty\">ObjectProperty</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that `P : ObjectProperty C` is codetecting if the functors `C(-, G)`\nfor `G : C` such that `P G` collectively reflect isomorphisms,\ni.e., if any `h` with codomain `G` such that `P G` uniquely factors through `f`,\nthen `f` is an isomorphism. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsCodetecting","kind":"def","line":96,"name":"CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsCodetecting","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L96-L102"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsDetecting\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">ObjectProperty</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsDetecting</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/ObjectProperty/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty\">ObjectProperty</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that `P : ObjectProperty C` is detecting if the functors `C(G, -)`\nfor `G : C` such that `P G` collectively reflect isomorphisms,\ni.e., if any `h` with domain `G` that `P G` uniquely factors through `f`,\nthen `f` is an isomorphism. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsDetecting","kind":"def","line":88,"name":"CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsDetecting","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L88-L94"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsCoseparating\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">ObjectProperty</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsCoseparating</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/ObjectProperty/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty\">ObjectProperty</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that `P : ObjectProperty C` is coseparating if the functors `C(-, G)`\nfor `G : C` such that `P G` are collectively faithful,\ni.e., if `f ≫ h = g ≫ h` for all `h` with codomain in `𝒢` implies `f = g`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsCoseparating","kind":"def","line":82,"name":"CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsCoseparating","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.lean#L82-L86"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsSeparating\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">ObjectProperty</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsSeparating</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/ObjectProperty/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty\">ObjectProperty</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that `P : ObjectProperty C` is separating if the functors `C(G, -)`\nfor `G : C` such that `P G` are collectively faithful,\ni.e., if `h ≫ f = h ≫ g` for all `h` with domain in `𝒢` implies `f = g`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Generator/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsSeparating","kind":"def","line":76,"name":"CategoryTheory.ObjectProperty.IsSeparating","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community